<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7649> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7649" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tribunus plebis of uncertain date, but if the Acilius, Censor, who gave him a nota (Fronto ad Caes. 5.26 [41]; 5.27 [42)) was M'. Acilius Glabrio (38). Cos. 67, and probably Censor 64, the date was ca. 64.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7649 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6639> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6639" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Tribune of the Plebs who was censured by a Censor named Acilius (Fronto Ad M. Caes. 5.41-42, 83 N). Note: No Censor of this name is known. Borghese therefore suggested that he was the unknown Censor of 64. There was however no lectio Senatus that year (Dio 37.9.4). The name Atilius, if it is meant, would bring into consideration the Censors of 247, 234, and 214. Cichorius (Untersuch. Lucil. 26f.) suggests Cornelius the Censor of 147. See Niccolini, FTP 438f." ;
	dprr:hasID 6639 .
